Test data show persistent race gap
The math record last week was welcome good news for the Washington D.C. public schools.
Although the Washington district is still far behind the country’s high-performance schools, the evidence shows that the fourth and eighth graders have made faster progress in the past two years than cities that include Atlanta, Chicago, and New York.
