Rhee said the district must continue to find better ways to meet the needs of the weak students.
This autumn, for example, some teachers are being trained to use a new reading curriculum, the Wilson reading system, aimed at students in the upper classes of primary and middle school, who have not mastered the basic skills of reading at the beginning of their school career and who are significantly behind their peers.
