For many years it was considered a secret city, inaccessible to Western visitors.
Selenograd, one of ten districts of the capital Moscow, was in the Soviet Union a strictly guarded location for secret military research.
Today, the commune with its 216 000 inhabitants, 37 kilometers from the center of Moscow, is considered the "Russian Silicon Valley".
