Scientific exchange
It is about a continuous scientific exchange.
But it is also about economic relations.
FIZ companies will be able to gain a foothold in the growing Russian market.
Conversely, Russian science companies want to secure orders in Germany.
Selenograd is the headquarters of important Russian research institutes and companies.
These include the Moscow Institute of Electron Technology, the major corporations Sitronics and Rosssiyskaya Elektronika.
The municipality was founded in 1958 as a so-called "socialist planning city" for armament research.
