According to Spanish legislation, a vehicle whose chassis number has been deregistered may no longer drive on the roads, but certain parts which are not damaged may be used as spare parts.
On the other hand, cars with historical value may be registered again, even if they have been cancelled after difficult administrative procedures.
Cost estimate of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in just four steps: Identification of the vehicle, search for the spare part, creation and creation of a cost estimate.
The ease of use of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially in order to convince the older professionals, who are usually more or less opposed to the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger vehicles, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with internet connection to use.
After the model to be repaired has been identified by the chassis number, a graphic of the respective model appears and then the required spare part is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price of working hours, surcharges or discounts, and then print out the cost estimate and pass it on to his customer.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool for peer review like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalog.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop oriented does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool is 350 euros a year, an amount that the customer can easily pay.
Currently, the company Audatex is working on offering these images in three-dimensional format.
This is an innovation that automechanics have been waiting for for a long time, since, for example, you can use it to select a door and then turn the picture completely around to look at the inside.
